HEADWORD: Dancing
<hw>Dan"cing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a. & vb. n.</pos> <def>from
<er>Dance</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dancing girl</b></col>, <cd>one of the women in the East
Indies whose profession is to dance in the temples, or for the amusement
of spectators. There are various classes of dancing girls.</cd> --
<col><b>Dancing master</b></col>, <cd>a teacher of dancing.</cd> --
<col><b>Dancing school</b></col>, <cd>a school or place where dancing is
taught.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dancy</ent>⟦br⟧
